DATE: It was used to fix the (year, month, and date) format.
 • Syntax: -> =DATE (month, date, year)

DAY: This provides the specific day. Syntax: =DAY(cell_name) 
EDATE: Provides the desired data in a specified format. Syntax: =EDATE((Starting_date,No of month))

NOTE: We must transform the date into a data format because Advance Excel stores the date as a serial number.

 WEEKDAY: It indicates the day of the specified date. 
   • WEEKDAY(cell_name) is the syntax.
HOUR: It solely provides the hour. Syntax: HOUR(cell_name)
MINUTE: It provides simply the minute. Syntax: -> MINUTE(cell_name)
